(1)	495 women and youths victims of insurgency in the North East reoriented and ready for placement in technical and vocational facilities for at least 6 months;
(2)	199 women and youth victims of violent conflicts in Benue and Plateau States trained on 10 trades and were supported to establish own businesses;
(3)	About 2,000 IDPs and host communities in 7 LGAs in Gombe State were supported with agro-inputs and agro processing equipment;
(4)	2.651 civil cases were resolved by the NSCDC;
(5)	40 security agencies, civil society organization and Operation Rainbow personnel were trained on the management of the EWER Platform ‘Jos Peace Platform’.
(6)	Trained women and youth on conflict prevention and peace building and formed ‘Community Youth Peace Committee’ in at least 10 violent ridden communities of 3 geo-political zones.
(7)	About 350 stakeholders sensitized on violent free general elections in 2015;
(8)	Provided technical and funding support to the work of the National Peace Committee which facilitated dialogues among key political office seekers in the 2015 general elections.  The effort of resulted in peace transition of government.

